info.name: Multilead Open API
info.description:
MultiLead Open API is a publicly available application programming interface used to perform different actions such as:

- adding leads to a campaign;
    
- collecting user data;
    
- getting read or unread messages;
    
- creating new global or non-global webhook users;
    
- and many more.
    

**ENDPOINT UPDATE - April, 2025**

- Update one or more variables for a lead in the specified campaign and LinkedIn account.
    

**NEW ENDPOINTS - February, 2025**

- Create Campaign From A Saved Sequence
    
- Create Lead Source & Link It To A Campaign
    
- Get User's Saved Sequences
    

**ENDPOINT UPDATE - January, 2025**

- Export Leads from a Specific Campaign (Now exports leads with both Sales Navigator and LinkedIn basic profile URLs)
    

**NEW ENDPOINTS - December, 2024**

- Change a Password
    
- Sync LinkedIn Messages
    
- Create a Team
    
- Create a Team Role
    
- Get Team Roles
    
- Get Team Members
    
- Invite a Team Member
    
- Update a Team Member
    

# Base API url

Please replace {{OpenAPIUrl}} with [https://api.multilead.io/api/open-api/v1](https://) on each endpoint that you wish to use.

urlencoded.description: (Required) This is the profile URL of the lead you wish to add.
(Required) This is the email of the lead you wish to add.
(Optional) This is the first name of the lead you wish to add.
(Optional) This is the last name of the lead you wish to add.
(Optional) This is a current occupation of the lead you wish to add.
(Optional) This is the phone number of the lead you wish to add.

(Optional) This action checks if the lead you wish to add already exists in the campaigns across all seats in the team.
If the "removeDbDuplicates": true, the lead won't be added to the campaign if they are found in any campaign across your team's seats. 
If the "removeDbDuplicates": false, the lead will be added even if they already exist in any campaign across the team's seats. 
If this parameter is not provided, the lead will not be added to the campaign if they already exist in any campaigns across the team's seats.
(Optional) This is an additional fields for personalization. For example: "personalizedField": ["twitter", "linkedinPersonalEmail"]
(Optional) This is an additional field for more information about the lead. For example: "country": "Germany"

variable.description: (Required Number) This is the ID of the campaign to which you wish to add leads.

query.description: (Optional) This action retrieves leads whose fullName, firstName, lastName, email, company, headline, occupation, currentCompany, or business email found by the platform matches the search parameter.

(Optional) This action retrieves leads with verified emails by the platform. Ensure 'filterByVerifiedEmails' is True and 'filterByNotVerifiedEmails' is False for it to work; otherwise, all leads will be retrieved.

(Optional) This action retrieves leads whose emails aren't verified by the platform. Ensure 'filterByNotVerifiedEmails' is True and 'filterByVerifiedEmails' is False for it to work; otherwise, nall leads will be retrieved.

(Optional) This action retrieves additional statuses in combination with ‘filterByStatus’. It can be used only when the ‘filterByStatus’ value is set to 4. For more information, check the ‘filterByStatus’ parameter description.
(Optional) This action retrieves leads from the campaign who are on specific steps.
(Optional) This action retrieves leads whose names contain the name you specify.
(Optional) This action retrieves leads whose company contains a company name you specify.
(Optional) This action retrieves leads whose occupation contains the parameter you specify.
(Optional) This action retrieves leads whose headline contains the parameter you specify.
(Optional) This action retrieves leads who have ‘Out of office’ status.
(Optional) This action retrieves leads whose ‘stepChangeTimestamp’ parameter is greater than the value you provide.
(Optional) This parameter retrieves specific leads and finds them through their id's you specify here.
(Optional) This parameter limits the number of results that you wish to retrieve. If not specified default value is 30.
(Optional) This parameter specifies a starting point for retrieving results from a dataset. If not specified, default value is 0.

(Required) This is the ID of the campaign from which you wish to get the lead info.

request.description:
This action retrieves specific leads from a chosen campaign that meet certain filter criteria.

There are **7 groups** of filters:

1\. **Advanced filters**: filterByName, filterByCompany, filterByOccupation, and filterByHeadline,

2\. **Filter leads by status**: filterByStatus, filterByConnectionDegree, and filterByOutOfOffice,

3\. **Filter by verified emails**: filterByNotVerifiedEmails, and filterByVerifiedEmails,

4\. **Filter by current step**: filterByCurrentStep,

5\. **Filter by selected leads:** filterBySelectedLeads,

6\. **Filter by step change timestamp**: filterByStepChangeTimestamp,

7\. **Search** (general filter).

**Filters** **within the same group** operate with the **OR** rule, meaning the platform retrieves leads who match at least one specified filter. For example, if you provide ‘filterByName’ and ‘filterByCompany’ from the Advanced Filters group, the platform will retrieve leads who match either ‘filterByName’ or ‘filterByCompany’.

However, **filters** **from two different groups** work with the **AND** rule, meaning the platform retrieves leads who satisfy both groups. For example, if you provide ‘filterByName’ from the ‘Advanced Filters’ and ‘filterByVerifiedEmails’ from the ‘Filter by verified emails’, the platform will retrieve leads that match both filters.

response.name: Success

(Optional) This action retrieves leads with verified emails by the platform. Ensure 'filterByVerifiedEmails' is true and 'filterByNotVerifiedEmails' is false for it to work; otherwise, all leads will be retrieved.

(Optional) This action retrieves leads whose emails aren't verified by the platform. Ensure 'filterByNotVerifiedEmails' is true and 'filterByVerifiedEmails' is false for it to work; otherwise, all leads will be retrieved.

(Optional) This action retrieves additional statuses in combination with ‘filterByStatus’. It can be used only when the ‘filterByStatus’ value is set to 4. For more information, check the ‘filterByStatus’ parameter description.

(Optional) This action retrieves leads who have ‘Out of office’ status.
(Optional) This action retrieves leads whose ‘stepChangeTimestamp’ parameter is greater than the value you provide.
(Optional) This parameter retrieves specific leads and finds them through their id's you specify here.
(Optional) This parameter limits the number of results that you wish to retrieve. If not specified default value is 30.
(Optional) This parameter specifies a starting point for retrieving results from a dataset. If not specified, default value is 0.

request.description:
This action retrieves specific leads from a chosen seat that meet certain filter criteria.

There are **6 groups** of filters:

1\. **Advanced filters**: filterByName, filterByCompany, filterByOccupation, and filterByHeadline,

2\. **Filter leads by status**: filterByStatus, filterByConnectionDegree, and filterByOutOfOffice,

3\. **Filter by verified emails**: filterByNotVerifiedEmails, and filterByVerifiedEmails,

4\. **Filter by selected leads:** filterBySelectedLeads,

5\. **Filter by step change timestamp**: filterByStepChangeTimestamp,

6\. **Search** (general filter).

**Filters** **within the same group** operate with the **OR** rule, meaning the platform retrieves leads who match at least one specified filter. For example, if you provide ‘filterByName’ and ‘filterByCompany’ from the Advanced Filters group, the platform will retrieve leads who match either ‘filterByName’ or ‘filterByCompany’.

However, **filters** **from two different groups** work with the **AND** rule, meaning the platform retrieves leads who satisfy both groups. For example, if you provide ‘filterByName’ from the ‘Advanced Filters’ and ‘filterByVerifiedEmails’ from the ‘Filter by verified emails’, the platform will retrieve leads that match both filters.

response.name: Success

item.name: Export Leads from a Specific Campaign

query.description: (Optional) This action export leads whose fullName, firstName, lastName, email, company, headline, occupation, currentCompany, or business email found by the platform matches the search parameter.

(Optional) This action exports leads with verified emails by the platform. Ensure 'filterByVerifiedEmails' is true and 'filterByNotVerifiedEmails' is false for it to work; otherwise, all leads will be exported.

(Optional) This action exports leads whose emails aren't verified by the platform. Ensure 'filterByNotVerifiedEmails' is True and 'filterByVerifiedEmails' is False for it to work; otherwise, all leads will be exported.

(Optional) This action exports additional statuses in combination with ‘filterByStatus’. It can be used only when the ‘filterByStatus’ value is set to 4. For more information, check the ‘filterByStatus’ parameter description.
(Optional) This action exports leads from the campaign who are on specific steps.
(Optional) This action exports leads whose IDs match the ones you specify.
(Optional) This action exports leads whose names contain the name you specify.
(Optional) This action exports leads whose company contains a company name you specify.
(Optional) This action exports leads whose occupation contains the parameter you specify.
(Optional) This action exports leads whose headline contains the parameter you specify.
(Optional) This action exports leads who have ‘Out of office’ status.
(Optional) This action exports leads whose ‘stepChangeTimestamp’ parameter is greater than the value you provide.

variable.description: (Required) This is your User ID.
(Required) This is the ID of the seat that the campaign in question is part of.
(Required) This is the ID of the campaign that you wish to export.

request.description:
This action exports specific leads from a chosen campaign that meet certain filter criteria.

There are **7 groups** of filters:

1. **Advanced filters**: filterByName, filterByCompany, filterByOccupation, and filterByHeadline,
    
2. **Filter leads by status**: filterByStatus, filterByConnectionDegree, and filterByOutOfOffice,
    
3. **Filter by verified emails**: filterByNotVerifiedEmails, and filterByVerifiedEmails,
    
4. **Filter by current step**: filterByCurrentStep,
    
5. **Filter by selected leads**: filterBySelectedLeads,
    
6. **Filter by step change timestamp**: filterByStepChangeTimestamp,
    
7. **Search** (general Filter).
    

**Filters within the same group** operate with the **OR** rule, meaning the platform exports leads who match at least one specified Filter. For example, if you provide ‘filterByName’ and ‘filterByCompany’ from the Advanced Filters group, the platform will export leads who match either ‘filterByName’ or ‘filterByCompany.’

However, **filters from two different groups** work with the **AND** rule, meaning the platform exports leads who satisfy both groups. For example, if you provide ‘filterByName’ from the Advanced Filters and ‘filterByVerifiedEmails’ from the Filter by verified emails, the platform will export leads that match both filters.

(Required) This is the ID of the seat where the desired campaign is located.

request.description:
This action creates a lead source and connects it to your desired campaign. To authenticate, use API key of the user who is associated with the seat where the desired campaign is located.

Required params for this endpoint are:

- userId - This is the ID of the user who owns the seat that contains the campaign where you want to send this lead source.
    
- accountId - This is the ID of the seat where the desired campaign is located.
    

When sending a request, make sure your body contains required leadSources array and provide exacly one lead source.

request.description:
This action provides information based on your Team Management role:

**\- For team members:** Retrieves information about the seats you've been invited to manage or own.  
**\- For co-workers:** Retrieves information about the seats that belong to the teams you manage.  
**\- For platform admins:** Retrieves information about the seats linked to the teams you own.

request.description:
This action retrieves all users associated with the chosen seat in any way. The way they are related to a seat determines their user types:

1. **Team Member**: Users who are invited to the team and assigned a seat with specific roles and permissions.
2. **Coworker**: Users who manage a team that owns a specific seat.
3. **Platform Admin**: Users who manage the entire platform to which the specific seat belongs.

This action retrieves all sequence templates (saved sequences) from a user who is a part of certain team. In other words, with this endpoint you'll get saved sequence template ID which you can use in "Create Campaign From A Sequence Template" endpoint. To authenticate, use API key of the user who belongs to a certain team.

Required params for this endpoint are:

- userId - This is the ID of the user whose saved sequences you want to retrieve.
    
- teamId - This is the ID of the team that the user is a part of.
